    "image_with_text_rYF4CM": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_czH6Rw": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Sanctuary",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_cWN9Km": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>LIGHT & BREEZY. RELAX & KICK BACK. HOME RESORT.</strong></p><p>Come home, exhale and enjoy the stillness and calm of your in-home relaxation hub. Unwind in a mellow bathroom of natural elements amidst personal design touches.</p><p>To create a home that feels like a sanctuary, focus on a soothing colour palette of soft whites, beiges, and greys, complemented by natural materials like wood and stone that add organic textures. Lighting plays a key role in creating the ambience you desire. Maximise natural light with large windows and opt for soft, ambient lighting. Incorporate soft textiles like cotton and linen, and bring the warmth of nature indoors with a touch of greenery.</p><p>In your bathroom, choose elegant fixtures like rain showers and freestanding bathtubs in sleek finishes. <a href=\"/collections/vanity-units\" title=\"Vanities\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Vanities</span></a> that feature wood textures and white countertops paired with chrome minimalist tapware are the perfect combo for this style. Alongside chrome, white tapware would work amazingly well to create the sanctuary of your dreams. Inspired by nature, the <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Nuage tapware range</span> by Phoenix Tapware boasts simplicity and tranquillity. </p><p>In order to create a kitchen sanctuary, opt for high-quality, natural materials such as granite for your <a href=\"/collections/sinks\" title=\"Sinks\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">kitchen sink</span></a> and wooden cabinetry. Incorporate state-of-the-art appliances in stainless steel or matte finishes and above all style your home with minimalism at the forefront of your design. Think glass vases with fresh flowers, wooden chopping boards and white sheer curtains.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "button_QeceGe": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "button_label": "Shop the Sanctuary Style Collection",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/sanctuary"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_czH6Rw",
