    "image_with_text_eDRGey": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_y7LBiT": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Modern Maximalism",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_hEKAKN": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>LOUD. UNIQUE. CHARACTER.</strong></p><p>Express your personal style through bold colours, patterns and contrast! Get creative and don’t be afraid to add some unique features to your home. Wow your guests with sleek finishes and bold statement features.</p><p>Maximalism in kitchen design embraces bold colours and eclectic patterns, creating vibrant and visually dynamic spaces. Rich hues like deep blues, vibrant reds, and emerald greens dominate, while a mix of diverse textures such as glossy tiles, rough-hewn wood, and smooth marble adds depth. Traditional freestanding appliances and extravagant sink mixers fit into the maximalist space by adding a sense of grandeur.</p><p>In bathrooms, maximalism continues with vivid colours, intricate patterns, and a variety of rich materials like marble and brass. Ornate mirrors, detailed vanities, and bold lighting fixtures create a sense of opulence, while plush towels, elegant accessories, and unique sink designs add layers of luxury. Think traditional tapware with matching accessories in bold brassy finishes alongside a black above counter basin. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "button_B79PXp": {
